hpicfMldMIB.name: hpicfMldMIB

revisions.description: Added commands to reset MLD if it is in error state.

Added objects hpicfMldIfEntryStartupQueryExpiryTime, hpicfMldIfEntryOtherQuerierInterval, hpicfMldIfEntryOtherQuerierExpiryTimex,compliance hpicfMldMIBComplianceV3 and group hpicfMldIfGroupV3. deprecated compliance hpicfMldMIBComplianceV2 and group hpicfMldIfGroupV2.
Added group specific query counter and MLD state

hpicfMldMIB.contactinfo: Hewlett-Packard Company 8000 Foothills Blvd. Roseville, CA 95747
hpicfMldMIB.description: This MIB module contains HP proprietary MIB definitions for managing MLD services including extensions to the standard MLD MIB (RFC 3019).

HpicfMcastGroupTypeDefinition.name: HpicfMcastGroupTypeDefinition
HpicfMcastGroupTypeDefinition.description: Type definition. This type distinguishes the different ways of tracking this device has for multicast joins. The method of tracking is primarily determined by the IGMP/MLD feature configuration. In particular if the snooping feature is enabled then port level tracking is the default which results in filtered groups. If the snooping feature is disabled then joins will result in standard groups being tracked by this device. When hardware resources are exhausted for multicast filtered bridging, joins may result in standard groups even though the snooping feature is enabled. Mini groups may be used when other resources, such as RAM, are low or exhausted.

hpicfMldControlUnknownMulticast.name: hpicfMldControlUnknownMulticast
hpicfMldControlUnknownMulticast.description: When enabled along with MLD, any IPv6 Multicast packets that are not joined by an MLD host will will be restricted to ports that have detected a multicast router or ports that are configured to always forward IPv6 multicast. When set to disabled or when MLD is disabled, the unjoined IPv6 multicast packets will be flooded out all ports in the VLAN. Permanently assigned multicast addresses are always flooded and so are not impacted by this object.

hpicfMldConfigForcedLeaveInterval.name: hpicfMldConfigForcedLeaveInterval
hpicfMldConfigForcedLeaveInterval.description: When a port's hpicfMldPortConfigEntryForcedLeaveFeature is enabled, this is the amount of time allowed for an MLD Report to arrive and cancel deletion of a multicast group requested by a previous MLD Leave request. Units are tenths of seconds.

hpicfMldMcastGroupJoinsCount.name: hpicfMldMcastGroupJoinsCount
hpicfMldMcastGroupJoinsCount.description: Current total count of Multicast groups joined.

hpicfMldIfTable.name: hpicfMldIfTable

hpicfMldIfEntry.name: hpicfMldIfEntry
hpicfMldIfEntry.description: HP extensions for an entry in the mldInterfaceTable.

hpicfMldIfEntryQuerierFeature.name: hpicfMldIfEntryQuerierFeature
hpicfMldIfEntryQuerierFeature.description: Turns MLD querier functionality on and off.

hpicfMldIfEntrySnoopingFeature.name: hpicfMldIfEntrySnoopingFeature
hpicfMldIfEntrySnoopingFeature.description: When enabled along with MLD, any IPv6 Multicast packets that are joined by an MLD host will be be restricted to ports which have received the joins. This can be overridden by other features like hpicfMldPortConfigEntryPortModeFeature.

hpicfMldIfEntryQuerierPort.name: hpicfMldIfEntryQuerierPort
hpicfMldIfEntryQuerierPort.description: Logical port which the querier is connected to. This is determined by the presence of querier packets on this port. This value is 0 if this device is querier.

hpicfMldIfEntryFilteredJoins.name: hpicfMldIfEntryFilteredJoins
hpicfMldIfEntryFilteredJoins.description: Current total count of groups on this interface being tracked on a per port basis. Traffic for these groups will be filtered to flow only to ports with active joins, subject to HW resource limitations such as the maximum number of groups supported by the hardware.

hpicfMldIfEntryStandardJoins.name: hpicfMldIfEntryStandardJoins
hpicfMldIfEntryStandardJoins.description: Current total count of groups on this interface being traced on a per interface basis. Traffic for these groups are flooded to the ports on the interface. These can come form joinees on interfaces which do not have MLD snooping turned on. They can also come from interfaces which have MLD snooping on, but HW resources have been exhausted for bridging traffic based on joins.

hpicfMldIfEntryPortsWithMcastRouter.name: hpicfMldIfEntryPortsWithMcastRouter
hpicfMldIfEntryPortsWithMcastRouter.description: This indicates which ports have a multicast router detected on them.

hpicfMldIfEntryOtherQuerierInterval.description: The length of time that must pass before a multicast router decides that there is no longer another multicast router which should be the querier on this interface.

hpicfMldCacheAddress.description: The IPv6 multicast group address for which this entry contains information.

hpicfMldCacheLastReporter.name: hpicfMldCacheLastReporter
hpicfMldCacheLastReporter.description: The IPv6 address of the source of the last membership report received for this IPv6 Multicast group address on this interface. If no membership report has been received, this object has the value 0::0.

hpicfMldCacheExpiryTime.name: hpicfMldCacheExpiryTime
hpicfMldCacheExpiryTime.description: The minimum amount of time remaining before this entry will be aged out. A value of 0 indicates that the entry is only present because mldCacheSelf is true and that if the router left the group, this entry would be aged out immediately. Note that some implementations may process Membership Reports from the local system in the same way as reports from other hosts, so a value of 0 is not required.

hpicfJoinedPorts.name: hpicfJoinedPorts
hpicfJoinedPorts.description: Logical ports with active MLD joins on them for this entry. For Filtered groups this will be the logical ports which have active joins. For standard and mini groups this will include all logical ports on the interface running MLD.

hpicfMldCacheStatus.name: hpicfMldCacheStatus

hpicfMldCacheFilterMode.name: hpicfMldCacheFilterMode
hpicfMldCacheFilterMode.description: The value indicates whether the group state is include(1) or exclude(2)

hpicfMldCacheExcludeModeExpiryTimer.description: The time remaining before the group in EXCLUDE state expires and transitions to INCLUDE mode.

hpicfMldCacheVersion1HostTimer.name: hpicfMldCacheVersion1HostTimer
hpicfMldCacheVersion1HostTimer.description: The time remaining until the local router will assume that there are no longer any MLD version 1 members on the IP subnet attached to this interface

hpicfMldCacheSrcCount.name: hpicfMldCacheSrcCount
hpicfMldCacheSrcCount.description: The number of sources either included or excluded for this group. If V1 host timer (hpicfMldCacheVersion1HostTimer) is active, this value will be zero.

hpicfMldPortConfigEntryPortModeFeature.name: hpicfMldPortConfigEntryPortModeFeature
hpicfMldPortConfigEntryPortModeFeature.description: The operational status of the MLD feature for this port or trunk. 1 implies that all IP Multicast traffic will be monitored on the port, 2 implies that IP Multicast traffic will be dropped on the port, and 3 implies that all IP Multicast traffic will be forwarded without the switch examining it.

hpicfMldPortConfigEntryForcedLeaveFeatur.name: hpicfMldPortConfigEntryForcedLeaveFeature
hpicfMldPortConfigEntryForcedLeaveFeatur.description: The operational status of the MLD feature for this port or trunk indicates whether any MLD Leaves received for an IPv6 Multicast group will cause the group to be deleted after the hpicfMLDConfigForcedLeaveInterval if no new MLD Reports are received for that group. Normal behavior is for a group issuing a Leave to be deleted after the Querier's Maximum Response time if no MLD Report is received.

hpicfMldPortConfigEntryFastLeaveFeature.name: hpicfMldPortConfigEntryFastLeaveFeature
hpicfMldPortConfigEntryFastLeaveFeature.description: The operational status of the MLD feature for this port or trunk indicates whether any MLD Leaves received for an IPv6 Multicast group will cause the group to be deleted immediately on single- connection ports. Normal behavior is for a group issuing a Leave to be deleted after the Querier's Maximum Response time if no MLD Report is received.
